"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-basketball-paris-olympics-2024-what-you-need-to-know-right-now-0\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  PublishedAug 11, 2024, 05:17 PM  UpdatedAug 11, 2024, 05:17 PM  PARIS - Sifan Hassan won the women's marathon, taking gold in an Olympic record time of two hours, 22 minutes and 55 seconds.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.004543721615939e-18, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hers was the first medal won on the last day of the 2024 Olympics, with more than a dozen up for grabs.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, Paris will pass the baton to Los Angeles during the closing ceremony, after a successful Games for the French that helped reboot the Olympic brand.\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3883971515580323e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999700985431, \"rank\": 2.628894117429089e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9342022990918964, \"rank\": 0.05184313340515642, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is what you need to know about the Olympics on Sunday.\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"DISTANCE QUEEN HASSAN  The Netherlands' Sifan Hassan deployed her famous late kick to win the women's marathon, adding the gold to her bronze medals in the 5,000 and 10,000 metres earlier in the week.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9095746367549542, \"rank\": 0.09859799378366796, \"text\": \"The Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 792, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hassan battled with Tigst Assefa of Ethiopia and managed to shake her in the last stretch to win by three seconds.\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 954, \"end\": 960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_Hassan_bin_Talal\", \"score\": 0.9840775215937233, \"rank\": 0.016061054527500562, \"text\": \"Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_Hassan_bin_Talal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_Hassan_bin_Talal\"}, {\"begin\": 990, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999831416063, \"rank\": 1.6304025036504698e-08, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FINAL DAY  It might be the final day but there are still 14 gold medals on offer, including in the men's and women's wrestling, the women's basketball and on the cycling track.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"DOMINATE THE RELAYS  The United States won the men's and women's 4x400 metres relays, cementing a dominant performance on the track by the Americans at this Olympics.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999777174, \"rank\": 1.4545577960297049e-11, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women won by more than four seconds, clocking the second-quickest time in history and stretching the country's victory streak in the event to eight in a row.\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men cut it a bit finer, just holding off Botswana on the finish line.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.99999998191106, \"rank\": 1.8088277635233294e-08, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's dominance in the women's sprinting came to an end in Paris.\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999445190917714, \"rank\": 5.548393399671124e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3883971515580323e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. SPOIL FRENCH DREAMS OF BASKETBALL FAIRYTALE  There was no \\\"Miracle on the Seine\\\" for France in the basketball as the United States ground out a 98-87 win to claim a fifth consecutive Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1809, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999231340583, \"rank\": 7.664598641527104e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1820, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9992340938599564, \"rank\": 0.000701894314905487, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q432