\"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James, the 39-year-old LA Lakers star, said he could not imagine himself playing at the Los Angeles 2028 Games.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2034, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9906489554591512, \"rank\": 0.00866803315862716, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 2057, \"end\": 2066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Lakers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.640936038684423e-36, \"text\": \"LA Lakers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Lakers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Lakers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TAIWAN'S LIN WINS BOXING GOLD  Taiwan's Lin Yu-ting, 28, one of two boxers at the centre of a gender eligibility row, beat Poland's Julia Szeremeta to claim the women's featherweight title.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lincolnshire\", \"score\": 0.999996197273458, \"rank\": 3.802740970135055e-06, \"text\": \"LIN\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lincolnshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lincolnshire\"}, {\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9993560232732982, \"rank\": 0.0006401618731242104, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9846341525000667, \"rank\": 0.015558809472126093, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2279, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"score\": 0.9387321027178633, \"rank\": 0.06526664218301244, \"text\": \"Julia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is unclear whether boxing will feature at the next Olympics.\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee ran the event at Paris after it stripped the International Boxing Association of its status as the sport's global body over governance and finance issues.\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2406, \"end\": 2437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2455, \"end\": 2460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3883971515580323e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2483, \"end\": 2515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4147483470236458e-23, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rival body World Boxing said national boxing federations needed to join its ranks to ensure the sport is included in the Los Angeles line up.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2611, \"end\": 2617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9999999996548468, \"rank\": 3.3829281367156536e-10, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 2715, \"end\": 2726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999700985431, \"rank\": 2.628894117429089e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"KIPYEGON'S GOLDEN HAT-TRICK  Kenya's Faith Kipyegon won her third straight Olympic 1,500 metres gold on Saturday, surging through the final lap to finish more than a second ahead of the field.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2766, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999560031948, \"rank\": 4.125588441993079e-08, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She cemented her status as one of the all-time great middle-distance runners, becoming the first athlete to claim three successive Olympic 1,500m titles.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Norway's Jakob Ingebrigtsen bounced back from his shock defeat in the 1,500 metres to win the 5,000 with a fierce final lap.\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3086, \"end\": 3092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.923015837607584, \"rank\": 0.08301148065121099, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. GYMNAST CHILES MAY LOSE MEDAL  American gymnast Jordan Chiles is set to lose her bronze medal in the women's artistic gymnastics floor exercise competition after the Court of Arbitration for Sport ruled in favour of an appeal by Romania's Ana Barbosu, who will move up to third place, it said on Saturday.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.4659290096854833, \"rank\": 0.7446465049551872, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MEDAL TABLE MACHINATIONS  Gol